        <td bgColor="black"><textarea cols="70" name="Message" rows="12" wrap="VIRTUAL">[quote]
Hello, I was kicking around some new possible AA skills we might see in PoP and was thinking Silence for Necro's might be really good.  If it was a 3 or 5 Tier upgrade skill and each upgrade increased Duration, Mob level susceptible, and decreased agro generated by imposing Silence on a mob etc.

Even if Verant thought Silence would be to powerful to be allowed to be cast on boss mobs it would be useful in raids if it were cast on guards and pets.  Silence them to keep from Chealing for example.  Seems like silence would fit in well with a Necro's mez abilities.  Maybe require spell casting subtlety 3 as a pre-req for it. 


I was also wondering if the Necro community had ever suggested an adaption to Life Burn so that a no fail Feign Death were put in right after the DD portion so that you dont draw instant low health agro and get killed before the healing DoT can save you.  250 points a tick is pretty useless against mobs that are doing quads and hate you.


Aj

 
[/quote]</textarea><br>
